.TH "async_schedule_node" 9 "async_schedule_node" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
async_schedule_node \- NUMA specific version of async_schedule
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "async_cookie_t" async_schedule_node
.BI "(async_func_t func "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ","
.BI "int node "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "func" 12
function to execute asynchronously
.IP "data" 12
data pointer to pass to the function
.IP "node" 12
NUMA node that we want to schedule this on or close to
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns an async_cookie_t that may be used for checkpointing later.
The node requested will be honored on a best effort basis. If the node
has no CPUs associated with it then the work is distributed among all
available CPUs.
.SH "NOTE"
This function may be called from atomic or non-atomic contexts.
